casebody.data:
John McNulty, Plaintiff in error, v. John Batty and others.

(See p. 72.)

Mr. Walker,

of counsel for the defendants in error, moved the court to direct the clerk to what court the mandate, or other process prescribed by the forty-third rule of court, should be addressed. On consideration whereof, it is now here ordered-by the court, that the clerk do not issue any mandate or other process in this case, but only a certified copy of the judgment this day rendered in this cause;
